-- U.K. Pound Depreciates to Less Than $1.50 for the First Time Since July 1
-- Daniel Tilles
-- 2010-07-12T06:20:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/u-k-pound-depreciates-to-less-than-1-50-for-the-first-time-since-july-1.html

          
          
             The pound fell to less than $1.50
for the first time since July 1.  
 Sterling weakened 0.6 percent to $1.4976 as of 7:19 a.m. in
London, and was little changed at 84.01 pence per euro.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Daniel Tilles in London at 
 dtilles@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        